Git vs Github 

Git = version control
- locally on pc 
-  tracks changes , able to commit , history on cli 
-  can be used offline 
- open source 

Github = Git repo hosting and collaboration 
-  runs on the cloud 
- able share code , edit , collaborate , open Pull requests 
- only online
- owened by Microsoft 

Git branching and merging:
Git branch - shows u the list of branches on ur repo and the one ur currently on 
Git checkout -b = creating new branch and switching 

Git switch -c = creating new branch and switching  ( newer syntax)
Git switch = just switching branches 

Git branch -d = deleting branch 
Git merge < dk-123 > = your on the dev (main) and are merging this feature branch in 

Fast forward vs recursive merges:
Fast forward merge = if main DEV has had no updates 
Recursive merge ( fix merge conflicts ) = if main DEV brnach has had changes since you branched off 

Rebase vs merge:
Merge = keeps history and is good for collaboration 
Rebase =  writes history to look cleaner but that can confuse people 
- cleaning up your local history 
